	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Absor Comments on Gems</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=386794" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Absor made some quick comments on the new mini-game 'Gems'. View the entire thread <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/065757.html" target="_blank">here</a>.
<blockquote>
<b>
<p>
Hello all,
<p>
I wanted to make a couple of quick comments about Gems.

People have been /petitioning and asking for resurrections and assistance over Gem-related deaths. Please don't do that. We will not be reimbursing anyone for deaths related to playing Gems. Please go to a safe place before playing Gems.
<p>
Also, there have been some rumors about in-game EverQuest prizes being awarded for high scores on Gems. Those are just rumors. There will be no prizes awarded for playing Gems.
<p>
Alan
</b>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
